genresAdvancedInfo.name: chilean black metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Chilean black metal is a subgenre of black metal that originated in Chile. It is characterized by its aggressive and raw sound, which is often accompanied by dark and atmospheric lyrics. The themes of the music are often related to anti-Christianity, Satanism, and occultism. The genre is known for its extreme and controversial nature, and has gained a following among fans of underground metal music.
